Package com.xd.cps2002.map

Enum TileType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TileType>
      • com.xd.cps2002.map.TileType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TileType>
    public enum TileType
extends java.lang.Enum<TileType>
    The TileType enum defines the different types of tiles used in different maps. It also defines the PlayerStatus after stepping on that particular tile. Each tile is described by its PlayerStatus, a handle (string identifier), and a colour (as three integers [r,g,b]).
    Author:
    Domenico Agius and Xandru Mifsud

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      Grass
      The Grass tile has a PlayerStatus of type PlayerStatus.Normal since nothing happens when the player steps on this tile.
      Treasure
      The Treasure tile has a PlayerStatus of type PlayerStatus.Death since the player should win the game when they step on this tile.
      Water
      The Water tile has a PlayerStatus of type PlayerStatus.Death since the player should restart the game when they step on this tile.

      • html_handle

        public final java.lang.String html_handle
        These two values describe the CSS style of the tile. The first, html_handle, is a simple string identifier used to reference the html_blurb. The blurb is what actually describes the CSS style of the tile.
